Exercise 3a

We need the sample statistics mean and std to fit the distribtuion.

# Compute mean and sd.
mean_T <- mean(T)
sd_T <- sd(T)

norm_T <- dnorm(T, mean = mean_T, sd = sd_T)

# Plot a histogram
hist(T, freq = FALSE)
lines(T, norm_T)

# plot(T, norm_T, type = "l")

Plot the empirical cdf of the sample and the parametric cdf in one panel.

# Want the cdf and the pnorm.

cdf_T <- pnorm(T, mean = mean_T, sd = sd_T)
plot(ecdf(T), verticals = TRUE, do.points = FALSE, xlab = "Temperature",
     ylab = "cdf", main = NULL)
lines(T, cdf_T)

Plot the quantile function of the fitten normal distribution. Draw a random number between (0, 1) and add this as a vertical line. Transform the random number using the quantile function of the normal distribution and add it as a vertical(horizontal) line.

x <- seq(0, 1, length = 201)
quan_T <- qnorm(x, mean = mean_T, sd = sd_T)
plot(x, quan_T, type = "l", ylab = "Temperature", xlab = "Probability")
rand <- runif(1, 0, 1)
abline(v = rand)
rand_trns <- qnorm(rand, mean = mean_T, sd = sd_T)
abline(h = rand_trns)

Exercise 3b

Plot a histogram, of sample. Add possion and geometric distribution.

ym <- as.yearmon(index(d))
y  <- as.numeric(aggregate(d$P, ym, function(x) sum(x > 15)))
y <- sort(y)
lambda <- mean(y)
prob <- 1 / (1 + lambda)

hist(y, freq = FALSE, main = "Nr of days with more than 15mm of precipitation")
lines(y, dpois(y, lambda), col = "blue")
lines(y, dgeom(y, prob), col = "green")
legend("topright", legend = c("Possion", "Geom"),
       col = c("blue", "green"), lty = 1)

Plot empirical cdf and cdfs of fitted distribtuion.

plot(ecdf(y), xlim = c(0, 6), verticals = TRUE, do.points = FALSE,
     xlab = "Nr of days >15 mm precipitation", ylab = "CDF", main = NULL)
ppois_y <- ppois(y, lambda)
# Not sure if this slice is the correct way to do it. But it kept complaining
# about the lengths.
ppois_step <- stepfun(y[2:99], ppois_y)
lines(ppois_step, xlim = c(0, 6), ylim = c(0, 1),
 vertical = TRUE, do.points = FALSE, col = "blue")

pgeom_step <- stepfun(y[2:99], pgeom(y, prob))
lines(pgeom_step, xlim = c(0, 6), ylim = c(0, 1), vertical = TRUE, 
do.points = FALSE, col = "green")

legend("bottomright", legend = c("ECDF", "Possion", "Geom"),
       col = c("black", "blue", "green"), lty = 1)

Compute expected values of the two fitten distributions, using the implemented densities, and compute the empirical mean of the sample.

helper_func <- function(x) {x * dpois(x, lambda)}
ex_pois <- sum(helper_func(y))

helper_func <- function(x) {x * dgeom(x, prob)}
ex_geom <- sum(helper_func(y))
ex_pois
## [1] 21.25763
ex_geom
## [1] 14.9496
lambda
## [1] 1.252525

Compute the variance of the distributions.

var_pois <- ex_pois**2 - lambda**2

var_geom <- ex_geom**2 - lambda**2
y_var <- var(y)
var_pois
## [1] 450.318
var_geom
## [1] 221.9218
